# YAITracker Workflow

The YAITracker MCP server (project key: **YAIT**) is the source of truth for all project management. Use MCP tools at every stage -- not as an afterthought.

## Issue Lifecycle

**Before starting work:**
- `list_issues` (project_key: YAIT, status: todo,backlog) to review the board
- `move_issue` to `in_progress`
- `add_comment` with a brief plan of what will be done

**During work:**
- `add_comment` to record significant decisions, blockers, or scope changes
- `create_issue` immediately when new work is discovered (never defer) -- include type, priority, story_points, estimated_hours
- `log_time` after completing meaningful chunks (not at the end -- as you go)

**After completing work:**
- `log_time` for any remaining unlogged time
- `add_comment` with a completion summary (what changed, files touched, tests added)
- `move_issue` to `done`
- If actual time differs from estimate by >50%, `add_comment` reflecting on why

## Estimation Discipline

- Every issue: `story_points` (fibonacci: 1,2,3,5,8,13) + `estimated_hours`
- Log time in real increments -- this feeds velocity analytics
- Use `update_issue` to adjust story_points post-completion if estimate was wrong

## Periodic Health Checks

At session start or milestone end, review and report:
- `get_project_health` (project_key: YAIT)
- `get_velocity` (project_key: YAIT)
- `get_estimation_accuracy` (project_key: YAIT)

## Issue Quality

- Titles: imperative mood, concise
- Descriptions: context (why), acceptance criteria, affected interfaces (MCP/API/UI)
- Types: bug, task, feature, improvement
- Priorities: urgent (prod down), high (blocks work), medium (next sprint), low (backlog)

## Git Integration

- Branch names reference the issue: `feature/YAIT-2-project-deletion`
- Commit body includes `Refs: YAIT-N`
